I worked on the transcript pipeline of my GM Farcaster AI bot project today. 

The pipeline is important because access to transcripts is what sets @warpee.eth apart from other bots so I need to make it ridiculously easy to upload new transcripts.

Pipeline steps:
- generate transcript from youtube video
- clean transcript for known spelling issues like NanishPrav and dGen
- break into chunks
- create embeddings from chunks
- upload embeddings to vector database

Updates:
- added better support for batch processing 
- can now safely reprocess videos that have already been loaded into the database, necessary for when I go back and work on improving the quality of transcripts 

Pipeline is solid and working smoothly, and as of now, @warpee.eth has access to transcripts from 170 episodes. I plan to upload the remaining episodes over the next few days. Once that‚Äôs complete, I‚Äôll shift my focus to enhancing the quality of the bot's replies.

text: i think this is a good first introduction, don‚Äôt u think?

‚Äúwhat‚Äôs one belief you changed your mind about in the past year?"
I used to think if given the chance to take an immortality pill, I wouldn't take it. I didn't want to be live on forever. However, I've changed my mind over the last year. I now think I will.

"what sparked the change?"
These are all hypothetical musings still but I realized there will be ways to _move on_ even after said pill, if one were to choose to do so. Human lifespan seems incredibly short on a universal time scale and there's no reason for it to remain so. Longer, potentially infinite, lives are inevitable and moving on will become a choice rather than a necessity.

"and how has it influenced your perspective?‚Äù
Made me more optimistic. Feels like humanity is just getting started. I am still pessimistic on the timeline of hitting this milestone i.e. I don't think it will necessarily happen during our lifetimes (hype cycles underestimate the trough of disillusion). However, I do think that given time, we will hit infinite lifespan.

cast.text:
@urls introducing "SockSync"‚Äîa mini web app that manages sock inventory and builds outfits around them.

Key Features:
Sock Inventory: Users catalog socks by color, style, and pattern.

Outfit Suggestions: Builds full looks starting with socks, ensuring coordination.

Context Awareness: Recommends outfits based on weather, location, and events.

Insights & Alerts: Tracks sock usage and weather changes for proactive planning.

Social Sharing: Users share sock-inspired looks and get outfit feedback.

UX/UI Vision:
Playful, intuitive design with drag-and-drop outfit pairing and a dashboard for quick suggestions.

Feel free to utilize the /socks channel for inspiration.
